properties.query:
// Contributor: Lucas Trainer & Innocent Wafula
// Reviewer: James Kim
// Reference: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/azure-resource-manager/management/azure-subscription-service-limits & https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/logic-apps/logic-apps-limits-and-config?tabs=azure-portal
//
// Description: Logic apps have a webhook limit of 1500 . In order to detect if we are close to hitting that limit, this query detects when logic app trigger "send data" exceeds more than 1000 operations per second.
// Handling Guidance: Evaluate sources sending data via webhooks to identify the top talker: change the bin operator below to | summarize WebhookCalls=count() by bin(TimeGenerated, 60s), LogicAppName
//
// Change notes
// ------------
// 05/15/23 James Kim - Promoted to CSGP and expanded results
//
let ingestion_delay = 1min;
let rule_look_back = 10min;
AzureDiagnostics
| where TimeGenerated >= ago(ingestion_delay + rule_look_back)
| where ingestion_time() > ago(rule_look_back)
| where Category == "WorkflowRuntime"
| extend TriggerName=Resource
| extend LogicAppName=resource_workflowName_s
| where TriggerName == "SEND_DATA"
| summarize TriggerActions=count() by bin(TimeGenerated, 60s), LogicAppName, TriggerName
| where TriggerActions >= 1000
